    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="612"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d612">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5831/253</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Swedish Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Boström</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-25">May 25,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honour to acknowledge receipt of your
                    note of May 25, 1935, referring to the question of the treatment of shipping,
                    which has been discussed during the negotiations leading up to the trade
                    agreement, signed to-day between the United States of America and the Kingdom of
                    Sweden.</p>
                <p>Due note has been taken of the suggestion by the Government of the United States
                    of America, that the subject of shipping should be dealt with in a separate
                    treaty.</p>
                <p>In accordance with instructions received, I have the honour to state that the
                    Government of Sweden, being likewise desirous of confirming the principle of
                    equality of treatment of shipping, which has been faithfully observed by the
                    United States of America and the Kingdom of Sweden, highly appreciate your
                    statement that the Government of the United States of America are prepared to
                    enter into negotiations looking to the conclusion of such a treaty.</p>
                <p>With renewed assurances [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. <hi rend="smallcaps">Boström</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
